"title": "5506: roof",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5506: roof",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Most buildings in biblical times had flat roofs. With the hot climate, they had a wider range of uses than merely providing shelter for the building.</p>\n<h2>Uses of roofs</h2>\n<h3>Shelter erected on the roof to make an extra room</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:10\">2KI 4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:22\">2SA 16:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:9\">PRO 21:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:24\">PRO 25:24</a></p>\n<h3>Guests lodged on the roof</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:8\">JOS 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:25-1Sam9:26\">1SA 9:25–9:26</a></p>\n<h3>The roof used as a place for leisure and relaxation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2\">2SA 11:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:29\">DAN 4:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:17\">MAT 24:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:15\">MRK 13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:31\">LUK 17:31</a></p>\n<h3>The roof used as a place of religious observance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:16\">NEH 8:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:12\">2KI 23:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:13\">JER 19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:29\">JER 32:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:5\">ZEP 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:9\">ACT 10:9</a></p>\n<h2>In cities, some roofs were open, public places</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa15:3\">ISA 15:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:50-Judg9:52\">JDG 9:50–9:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:24\">2SA 18:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:38\">JER 48:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:26-Matt10:27\">MAT 10:26–10:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:2-Luke12:3\">LUK 12:2–12:3</a></p>\n<h2>Roofs were usually constructed with a thick layer of clay</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:4\">MRK 2:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:19\">LUK 5:19</a></p>\n<h2>Roof as a synonym for house</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:8\">MAT 8:8</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:6\">LUK 7:6</a></p>",
